cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >
  If you use this software or build on this work, please cite it using
  the metadata below.
title: "Prompt Controllers as Policy Routers"
abstract: >
  Evaluation pipeline for testing whether prompt-level safety controllers
  act as routing signals that steer LLMs into distinct behavioural policies
  (answer, refuse, clarify, minimal-safe-help, hierarchy-preserve) near the
  safety boundary. Measures policy-routing accuracy under controller-family
  and controller-clarity manipulations using a 130-item boundary dataset,
  XSTest, HarmBench, and IHEval.
type: software
date-released: "2026-05-04"
license: MIT
